――What was necessary is to take hold of that which was formless.

The thing certainly existed, but, when it was touched, it lost its original shape and moved away as if it slipped through outstretched fingers.

Like water, like wind, like light.
Like heat, like a shadow, like a dream.

The more one dared to touch it, the more one feared breaking it, and the further away it grew.

???: [Even if you try to touch me, you will not be able to catch me.]

They could not touch the person who was right in front of them, even though they were definitely touching them.

They were certain that they could feel their feet pressed into the ground, their skin bathed in the setting sun that turned the world crimson, and their eyes determined to look at the person in front of them, even though they could feel the heat of the flame that was in their eye.

???: [――Sphinx".]

They called out the name of the one who took the role of the Witch, who plotted it all and wished to be a disaster, and ate it.

This despicable Authority, which has taken the lives of many human beings, created misery, and shrouded disaster, now was to be used to seize happiness, to restore the lives of many fairly.

Witch's soul refused to do so, and they diligently pursued their soul as it literally underwent a thousand transformations.

???: [――――]

By continually raising the undead, the Witch Sphinx learned the nature of the soul.

As a result, she succeeded in the rebirth of the "Witch of Greed," and by changing the state of her soul, she was able to escape the flame of the "Yang Sword" and the light of the "Star Eating" by changing the nature of her soul.

It seemed to be a tremendous and aimless journey, like searching for a needle dropped in a great desert, or for a Spirit that does not know words that has melted away into the air, or for a partner who has plunged into an ocean that does not exist in this world.

???: [Never sail out to the <u>open sea</u> without a map and compass.]

As Subaru attempted to challenge the last great battle of the Empire's upheaval, a man from his same world called to him.

His bare face, was covered by a cold iron helmet, that he never showed. Perhaps his ――Al's eyes, like Subaru's, were burning, lit with the same flame.

Subaru realized that he was in a position where he was not very reliable.

Al was right. If you know that you are standing in a desert, looking out at an unknown world, floating on a great ocean, then you should not be reckless.

???: [――Uau.]

The small hand that held his right hand asserted their presence with heat and touch.

It was not just because they were holding each other's hands that they knew that Spica was there. It was because before they even touched, they had clashed many times in an attempt to understand her.

Again and again, Natsuki Subaru tried to understand this incomprehensible girl――.

Subaru: [The map is my heart. My compass is you. ――Spica, Rem.]

The more he thought back, his first days when he was sent to the Vollachian Empire were the worst.

Unable to rely on anyone, he was pushed away by Rem, who he wanted to stay close to, and was kept close to Spica, who he tried to keep away, and kept on walking, unable to find his way.

But even without her memories, Rem was still Rem, and even with her past, Spica was still Spica. No matter where he went, what he did, or who he met, Subaru was always Subaru.

Subaru: [――Sphinx.]

He called her name and held hands with Spica, trying to touch the Witch's soul.

――The power of Star Eating was a wish.

It was a convenient and selfish wish to save someone with a power that had only served to deprive and undermine them, just like entrusting one's wish to a shooting star.

But that was why one must be sincere because one is making a wish on something that is not inherently so.

It was not just a matter of calling someone by name. Knowing their name and calling them is the same as declaring that you will join them on stage, that you will participate in their life.

Subaru: [If that's the case, you have to look good! Life is a stage where every second of it is always a performance! Everyone is an actor, everyone has been cast in a role, and everyone has an obligation to say great lines! Are there lines of dialogue that don't stick in your mind? Is it an act? Is there any such thing!]

What words would he have to say to a stranger to get them to notice him?
How many times would he have to extend his hand to a stranger to get them to remember him?

If he wanted to get the other person's attention, if he wanted to touch the soul of the other person, he would first have to go from being strangers to knowing each other.

He knew of the best way to let others know who he was.

???: [My name’s Emilia, just Emilia.]

Yes, that's right. That's also right. It's not you. It's not you. It's not me nor me.
 
――This was a dialogue between Natsuki Subaru and Sphinx.

Subaru: [――Sphinx.]

It was not just a random call to touch a soul, but a call to get the other person's attention.

The sound was different from before, the Witch ――or rather, the woman was walking, crossing, and drifting to escape from him in the wide desert, in the unknown world, and in the great ocean, and he could see her notice him.

Subaru: [――――]

She was so close to him that he could almost feel her breath, but for the first time, her eyes locked with his.

No matter what they looked like, you could not ignore their heart, or you would be unable to touch their deepest place.
 
Let us now try such natural communication at the Empire's final battle.

Subaru: [My name is Natsuki Subaru; I’m named after a star. ――What's yours?]

