――Natsuki Subaru and Spica faced off against the Witch, Sphinx.

As Subaru and Spica strove to seize the soul of the vindictive and tenacious Witch, Al's mission was to keep the enemy at bay so as to prevent any interference.

???: [Ah, bring it on! Ain’t nobody gonna beat me or the Princess!]

Spurring himself on while roaring thus, Al continued to swing his improvised dao.

Behind Al, Sphinx was seated with her back against the wall, and flumped before her with his legs crossed was Subaru, who remained facing her head-on.

What Subaru was attempting to do in cooperation with Spica was an idea beyond the pale even for Al.  

Hearing of the terrible idea of relying on the Authority of Gluttony had made Al question their sanity, but in fact, discerning that Subaru would be able to do it, Priscilla had ordered them to proceed.

If that is what would lead to the future, then Al would support them to his utmost. And ensure that it was achieved.

???: [Ul Goa.]

From above Al’s head, Roswaal flying freely across the sky rained down fire.

Though it was not the highest level of magic, casting that much magic in rapid succession was no ordinary feat. However, even his extraordinary magical prowess was unable to overwhelm the opponent he was presently attempting to restrain.

???: [Ul Huma.]

Countering the pouring rain of fire, was a barrage of water that had been shot into the sky from the ground.

In terms of number and effective range, both being the world’s top-class users, this was magical warfare at a level rarely seen in modern times――The Magician and the Witch each having sided with the world, turned the world against each other, and used each other’s world as their own.

Though Priscilla had vociferously asserted her presence, it was not the case that all the Witches had been drawn to her like moths to a flame. Some of the Witches, realizing that the Yang Sword was not the only thing they needed to fear, had joined in this juncture.

However――,                             

???: [If that’s how it is, so be it, in fact!]

With the appearance of a young girl and the movements of an athlete, Beatrice, with her right eye aflame, had cast Yin magic. 

Instantly, her upraised hands birthed a pale purple haze over the whole area, slowing down the movements of the attacking Witches as well as the undead that, lacking self-awareness, had impulsively charged forth upon her command.

Al took advantage of that nice assist from Beatrice with great vigor.

Al: [Your stars were bad indeed!]

The exquisite magic control weakened the enemy, bestowing a period of invincibility solely upon Al. As he beheaded the pitiable undead one after the other, at Beatrice who had supported him, Al winked through his helmet.

That very moment, at the wink that should not have been visible to her, Beatrice had a change of expression.

Beatrice: [This is bad, I suppose!]

At her words, Al turned around with a "Huh?", and saw something――a massive fragment with a purple glow, in the scale of tens of meters, hurtling towards them as it bounced off the ground.

Al had no idea that this was the slashed-off tip of the great sword wielded by the Giant Magic Crystal Soldier that Priscilla and the others were fighting. What he did know, was that a direct hit from that fragment, would result in Al along with Subaru and the others behind him altogether becoming minced meat――,

Al: [Must――]

Escape with Subaru and the others from the trajectory of the flying fragment.

How many attempts would be needed, he did not know, and neither did he have the time to make such an estimation. Everything was more of trial and error at the precipice of life and death rather than a theoretical treatise. 

Al: [Matrix Update, Thought Experiment――]

???: [――Don't'cha give up jus’ like that!!]

A moment later, passing by Al, a powerful arm plunged into the fragment, intercepting it.

A roar and a torrential wind escaped behind him, but the flying debris was held in place. It was Garfiel who did it, biting his sharp canine teeth.

Garfiel: [Sorry for being late, Beatrice! Captain…]

Beatrice: [ You did well meeting us in fact! Protecting Subaru and Spica is our win condition I suppose.]

Garfiel: [Ha! That’s easy to understand. Just like, “If you whisper of love, follow the King of Thorns.”]

Kicking at the huge piece of debris that he had stopped, Garfiel punched his fists together in front of his chest. Garfiel also had his eyes, not figuratively but literally, burning and his whole body was filled with vigor in response to his will to fight.

Witch: [ Retreat: Required.]

A quiet voice announced the Witch's entry into the war, and Al and the others looked up to see a scene of swirling lights in the sky. The vortex of light had some kind of gravitational pull, and the surrounding buildings and debris floated up, were swallowed by the vortex, and then was crushed and turned into light dust.

The power of destruction was felt in the light dust itself, and with a voice from the Witch, it was able to equalize the ground――

Tanza: [ Halibel-sama, please would you kindly,]

Halibel: [That's fine. I'm always happy to help a hard working girl.]

Suddenly, two different voices were heard, and in the next moment, a cannonball in a kimono――no, a deer girl, flew by.

The girl spun herself in the air and kicked the Witch's back as she was on the verge of raining light dust. The momentum and force of the kick shattered the poor Witch in half.

Halibel: [Yea, yea, that's a great feat. With a girl like you, the future of the Empire is secure.]

With the same momentum, the girl was about to dive into the vortex of light but was saved just in time by the jet black wolf man.

The wolf man rendered harmless the vortex of light the Witch had prepared with a quick piercing hand, softly catching the girl with the same hand that did so, and then descended to the ground.

The same wolf man who threw the girl and the same wolf man who caught her was responsible for her confusion.

Tanza: [A new monster has been added! A Cecilus type!?]

Halibel: [Can't deny that, but that's an unpleasant classification.]

Tanza: [It has been a while. I am sorry to be presumptuous, Cecilus-sama and Halibel-sama are very different in their nature that it would be disrespectful.――Why don't we protect Schwartz-sama?]

Al: [Oh, oh. You're quick on the uptake! And I'll definitely welcome strong guys.Let's protect Bro together!]

Halibel: [Yea. Looks like we’re almost at endgame, and it looks like we even received this gift.]

Tanza, a girl in a kimono seen in the Demon City――greeted the wolf man Halibel. Both of them have Priscilla's blessing in their eyes as a flame, which was very encouraging.

Additionally――,

Beatrice: [I don't know where this came from or who, but I just received the perfect souvenir, in fact.]

Saying this, Beatrice touched a huge piece of debris with her small palm.――The rubble that Garfiel had stopped, it was not just a piece of rubble, but a block of magic crystal stone.

Beatrice disassembled it into mana in one breath, and about a hundred swords made of amethyst crystals appeared all around her at once, and the sword dance began with the movement of her hand as she lifted it.

Beatrice: [Betty will use her abundant mana in this way, I suppose. You guys, if you even scratch Subaru, you will be mercilessly punished, in fact.]

Tanza: [If that were to happen, I will be the one to deliver Beatrice-sama's punishment!]

Al shrugged when he saw both Beatrice and Tanza's sparking gazes.

――Apparently, Subaru's unharmed state should also be included in the updated matrix’s conditions, he thought.

△▼△▼△▼△

Thus, protected by Al and the others, Subaru is in the midst of extreme concentration.

He was not unconscious, nor was he in a dream. Nevertheless, the battle going on around him was outside his awareness, and his awareness was not of the Imperial Capital.

Currently, Natsuki Subaru's existence is not on the battlefield of Imperial Capital, but in a white world where there existed only himself, Spica, who was holding his hand, and Sphinx, who was looking directly at him.

――It was a space that could easily be mistaken for the Hall of Memories.

Subaru: [I suppose for me, this is mainly a place of bad memories.]

It was a place where he arrived unintentionally and where his memories were forcibly consumed.

It was fresh in my mind that he gave Emilia and Beatrice a hell of a lot of hard time and made a mess of Ram and Julius.

Above all, this is the place where "Natsuki Subaru" disappeared.

Subaru: [But that's the whole reason why I am here.]

Spica: [U?]

Subaru: [You don't need to know about this place. It's a bit of a mess as far as you're concerned. And that’s fine.]

Subaru smiled at Spica's puzzled expression, and then drew in a deep breath.

Subaru met Spica and Sphinx in this white, tranquil space, not because they were all friends whose names began with the letter S. 

This was because all of them had close connections with "themselves" and wanted to talk in private with them.

Witch: [Sphinx was the name of the monster that was in my creator's knowledge.]

Subaru: [Hm? Oh, that's how you got your name.]

Witch: [Yes. If my creator's wishes had been fulfilled from the beginning, I would have been named Echidna. Since that did not happen, it became necessary to have another name.]

Directly facing him, Sphinx was surprisingly calm and told Subaru about her origins.

Sphinx --as Subaru knew it, was a monster with the body of a lion and the head of a man. It guarded the pyramids and gave the impression that it was good at giving riddles.

Subaru: [What goes on four feet in the morning, two feet in midday, and three feet in the evening?… Do you know what this is?]

Witch: [――? A monster? Or a shape-shifting monster, perhaps.]

Subaru: [You'd think so. And by the way, the answer is man.]

When he told them a traditional riddle, both Sphinx and Spica looked at him with reluctance. They were not convinced, but he would have liked to direct their complaints to a different Sphinx who presented the riddle.

In any case――,

Subaru: [Thanks for letting me know. In exchange, I have something to show you, too.]

Witch: [What do you want me to see?]

Subaru: [Yeah. ――Although I'm not sure if you'll be happy with it.]

After that preface, Subaru smiled a little and then glanced at Spica. As if to allay Subaru's fears, she lifted her hand, still clasped in hers, and said, "U!".

This was Spica's way of saying they had come to terms with "themself" a step ahead of Subaru.

――When he closed his eyes in the "Hall of Memories," he could strongly smell his own scent.

He has heard that there is a strong connection between memories and smells. Many memories are associated with smells, which may be why the Hall of Memories gave such an impression.

In either case, Subaru slowly tried to follow his own scent and walk through the unreal Hall of Memories to bring the uncertain to the certain.

In one of the many Return by Death attempts, Olbart, who had lost both arms, apologized in a casual tone of voice for the difficulty in undoing his infantilization ――So instead of an apology, Subaru asked for guidance. 

The vessel and the soul were eager to return. Now all that there was left to do was to use smell as a guide to lead them.

If he did that――,

Subaru: [――My name is Natsuki Subaru. The one and only, broke beyond compare in the world and heaven.]

Yes, the voice, which was making trivial remarks, became a little deeper and lower. His eye level changed, and the feel of Spica's hand in his grip suddenly felt smaller and smaller.

However, it was the opposite: Spica did not shrink. ――Subaru changed.

Subaru: [――――]

A sensory, change. His soul was in a constant state of seeking to return to its own original form.

The feeling of accomplishment, like the growing pains in the heart and soul, having literally grown from a child to an adult, seeped through Subaru's blood vessels and nerves and into every cell of the body.

And so, having regained a solid sense of self, Subaru once again faced Sphinx ――or rather, faced Sphinx head-on for the first time.

Witch: [――Nice to meet you, Natsuki Subaru.]

Having observed the change, Sphinx, following Subaru's intention, greeted him for the first time. Upon hearing that, Subaru thought that maybe they were the one who could talk.

Natsuki Subaru thought so with his now restored mind, body, heart, and soul.

Subaru: [But we have to settle things.]

Witch: [Yes, we do.――Parting: Required.]

Subaru: […Why is that?]

Witch: [Why, what do you mean why?]

Subaru: [Why are you trying to do it all on your own?]

That was Subaru's honest question.

The Witch Sphinx caused the "Great Disaster" that destroyed the Vollachian Empire, tampered with many lives, and did many things that would have otherwise been unforgivable. But was it necessary to do so?

If the Sphinx's only purpose was to reproduce her creator ――the Witch of Greed.

Subaru: [You could have done it a different way. You made mistakes in the way you did things. If only you hadn't done it the wrong way, we could have,]

Witch: [You think we could have avoided fighting? That would have been impossible. Reconsideration: Required.]

Subaru: [Why not!]

Witch: [Because there is a certain reason, other than the reproduction of my creator, that is in me.]

Sphinx looked down at herself, smiled faintly, and proclaimed a crucial difference.

Subaru could see the smile, a sign that Sphinx was congratulating herself, and he could no longer resist.

But at the same time, Natsuki Subaru definitely, clearly, found it.

Spica: [Uau.]

Subaru: [Yeah, I know. ――Thanks, Spica.]

Spica called out to Subaru, who bit his lip. She probably would have liked to react to Subaru returning to his original size, but she held back and was considerate.

He wanted to respond to that desire. ――Even if he had to go to hell to do so.

Subaru: [――Sphinx.]

Witch: [What is it? I don't care what――]

Subaru: [Happy Birthday.]

With that said, he touched Sphinx, whose eyes opened at the unfamiliar congratulation.

And then――,

△▼△▼△▼△

Basking in the wind carrying a pleasant evening fragrance, Priscilla gave her cheers to existence.

She had been elated by the dinner banquet between Sphinx, who, using the mechanisms of the Crystal Palace Meteor, had gone berserk with the upstood Giant Magic Crystal Soldier, and the Generals who had been assembled by Vincent.

She wished to continue beholding it as a dream that one would not wake up from, as a program that would not come to a close, as a story with no “<u>endhing</u>”.

However, since that childish “<u>iigo</u>” was not appropriate for the curtain falling on this battle――,

Priscilla: [In a manner most befitting, it is I who shall lower the curtain.]

Saying that, Priscilla let go of Arakiya’s hand as they flew above the clouds, and began falling through the sky.

Plummeting straight downwards, Priscilla returned the Yang Sword to the sheath of the sky, and basking in the setting sun with her arms spread out, she closed her eyes.

Even if she could not see them, the souls of those whom she had shared the flame of her soul with were transmitted to her as if whispered intimacies from the world.

Arakiya, clad in bands of light, repelled  the Witch’s magic, and the Dragon, covered in armor of cumulus, contained her so that the damage would not spread outside of the city. Standing harmoniously with the husband she had reunited with, Yorna was busy smashing up the ground in a radical expression of love, having no hesitations about possessing her daughter’s eye.

And, as an incompetent older brother, the Vollachian Emperor, Vincent Vollachia――,

Vincent: [Tardy.]

With a brief utterance, he looked up at the Giant Magic Crystal Soldier undaunted with his sable eyes. The Giant Soldier raised its two magic crystal greatswords overhead, and was about to attempt cutting down the apex of the Empire along with the entire Imperial Capital.

Thereupon, Lightning came piercing through from behind Vincent――,

???: [――Bear witness, Observers of the heavens above. ――Witness the choices the world shall… Nay! Witness as it chooses me!]

Two streaks, one the white gleam of a blade, and the other a black light of severance, the flash of blades capable of severing the light of stars and the logic of curses bolted through the sky.

With that, the omen of the Imperial Capital’s devastation that was the Giant Magic Crystal Soldier had its arms lopped off from its shoulders. With a thundering tremor and eruption of smoke, the brilliance of the magic crystals was reduced to dust, and the flash of Dream Sword and Fiend Sword severed their existence.

Even so, the Giant Soldier, having lost its arms, was still wielding the countless swords floating in its vicinity, and was attempting to prune the defiant will of the Empire.

Of course, that aim included the falling Priscilla.

???: [――Priscilla Barielle.]

Enough to paint over the hue of the sky, the light of ruination forcibly shone through her eyelids. Sensing that it	approaching herself, Priscilla opened her eyes, and reached her hands ought to her left and right sides.

The next instant, Priscilla caught the Yang Swords of the Wise Emperor and the King of Thorns in her right and left hands respectively, and with a swing of the twin swords, she scorched the Witch’s magic crystal swords to naught in one fell swoop. The swords, bursting into flames in a chain reaction, swirled around the Giant Magic Crystal Soldier, blanketing the sky in a crimson curtain of flame.

Priscilla: [――――]

For a moment, Priscilla’s figure disappeared from everybody’s sight―― the figure of the Sun Princess perforated the curtain of flame, and shot directly towards the sealed magic crystal bud within the Giant Magic Crystal Soldier’s head.

It was an act accomplished thanks to the three Yang Swords―― riding upon her own Yang Sword, which had been launched out of the sheath of the sky, Priscilla soared with the Yang Swords of her brother and forefather in hand.

――The Yang Sword upon which Priscilla rode, its tip thrust into the magic crystal bud, tearing through the closed flower petals and making its way inside.

???: [――Priscilla Barielle.]

That instant, the barrage of light orbs intended to intercept her, was cleared away by the King of Thorns’s Yang Sword.

As flame enshrouded her field of vision, Priscilla stepped down to the floor and advanced.

???: [――Priscilla Barielle.]

Simultaneously, stepping past the flames enshrouding her vision, Sphinx rushed out with a sword of light in hand.

The two met gazes, and Priscilla burned away her opponent’s sword with the Wise Emperor’s Yang Sword.

Sphinx: [――Priscilla Barielle.]

Eyes burning with fury, Sphinx had called her name many times, to which Priscilla smiled. Perceiving that smile in her vision, Sphinx leaped backwards, and readied her two hands.

Birthing ten blades of light upon her fingers, she rampaged about within the bud; irregularly reflecting off the inside of the magic crystals, the kaleidoscope of Death gleamed with beauty.

At the chaotic and emotional scintillation, Pirscilla raised both her hands towards the heavens.

Then, gripping the treasured sword protruding beyond her outstretched hands――,

Sphinx: [――PRISCILLA BARIELLE!]

Priscilla: [That is mine name.]

Within the sonorous bellow of that voice, there was a certain heat tinged with enmity. Thereupon, Priscilla swung down the brilliant dazzling Yang Sword.

――The flash of scintillating flame, that light reminiscent of sunrise or daybreak, of a new dawn, ardently shone upon her life. As the interior of the magic crystal bud was illuminated, it began to bloom.

That was to say, the sprouting of a soul――,

Priscilla: [Stand tall, Sphinx.]

Sphinx: [――――]

Priscilla: [As none other than your very self, you fulfilled the role of mine enemy. ――It is a great service.]

Adjusting her posture after swinging the Yang Sword, Priscilla spoke thus to Sphinx, who was standing in front of her. Receiving that, Sphinx narrowed her black eyes, and,

Sphinx: […Despite having failed to succeed, is that so?]

Priscilla: [A matter of course. Just who do you take mineself for?]

Scoffing at the question, Priscilla responded so.

At her answer, Sphinx lowered the edges of her eyebrows, and heaving a sigh with an expression that had lost its sternness,

Sphinx: [Priscilla Barielle. ――The fateful enemy of myself, the Great Disaster, Sphinx.]

As a being who had found meaning in her existence differing to the original reason for which she had been created, she smiled.

――That was the conclusion between the Sun Princess, Priscilla Barielle, and the Great Disaster, Sphinx.

△▼△▼△▼△

Once, before, they were nearly dead.

Even then, there was a goal that could not be fulfilled, but they accepted it without equanimity that in that end, they would not reach it, and their heart felt as calm and worthless as though it were joining in the evening’s setting sun.

So now, what about now?

???: [Just like before, I will disappear without fulfilling my wish――]

Their heart was like that of a child longing not for the setting sun but for the rising one, and could feel a certain heat burning in their chest, pulsing through their un-beating body.

And then, they were told that this was the true nature of the horrible "heat" that had dazzled in the eyes of the cold and parched monster in that place where they had been bound to for decades.

???: [Thank you. For teaching me who I am. ――Gratitude: Required.]

An ill-defined, uncertain, and ambiguous self is formed as themself, which is far from what they had originally wanted to become, and yet they did not dislike it.
 
Once again, it can be said. This newly born existence as a monster was not a replacement for the Witch of Greed.
 
So now that they were disappearing without their own personal wishes fulfilled, they spoke.

???: [――Ahh, how frustrating.]

△▼△▼△▼△

???: [――Sphinx.]

Subaru called out her name, and Spica, having touched her soul, had devoured her existence.

The moment Star Eating activated, welling up within Subaru was a mellow sense of satisfaction and accomplishment, along with a feeling of loneliness. It was perhaps, something like the kind of loneliness felt at the end of a meal filled with laughter.

Truly fulfilling, and yet slightly lacking, it was that kind of a moment.

???: [――――]

He had congratulated her on her birth as one life, and with that same mouth he had helped devour her.

However, it was not out of hatred. To make her suffer, or to disappoint her, he had not wanted to do either. There just was no other way to conclude this. 

The resolution between Subaru’s group and Sphinx, this was the only way it could be.

???: [U!]

Rustling, Sphinx turned to dust and disappeared. As he witnessed her demise, Spica, who had brought it about with Subaru, called out to him.

To Spica, words of gratitude and appreciation must be given.

Subaru: [Besides, that the enemy leader is no more, Abel and the others also――]

As he attempted to stand up while he spoke.

???: [――Subaru.]

The voice, heard unexpectedly, ignored Subaru's eardrums and cranium, and resonated directly into his brain.

It had always been like that. That beautiful silver-bell like voice, always laid Natsuki Subaru bare. And having made the bared Subaru turn around, it had brought with it the urge to burst into tears.

Subaru: [――――]

Unable to speak, as Subaru stood up and turned around, the glow of the setting sun shone into his eyes. That sunset, which had brought with it the afterglow of victory, had become a hindrance. ――For within that light, there was a face he longed to see.

Her long silver hair that resembled the dew drops of a night sky’s moon, her eyes of amethyst, the most beautiful jewel in the world, from the top of her head to the tips of her toes, there was not one bit that he did not find lovely.

Spica: [Uau.]

Subaru was almost in tears from the longing that had welled up within him, and Spica, who had let go of his hand, patted him on the back.

With the touch of that palm providing the opportunity and the courage, Subaru started to run.

He passed by Al who gave him a thumbs up, he sent a thankful gaze at the purple smoke puffing Halibel, he patted the shoulders of Garfiel who was balling his eyes out in Subaru’s stead, he poked the cheek of Beatrice as she held back her urge to jump onto him, and he smiled wryly at Tanza who had bowed deeply, after which Roswaal, who had descended from the sky, took off his jacket and draped it over him.

???: [Subaru-kun, aren’t you compleeetly~ naked.]

Having grown back, Subaru's clothes from his infantile state not longer fit. If this had been his original world, it would be like not having the clothes to go buy clothes. 

But this was not his original world, this was another world, the one in which Subaru now lived.

Emilia: [Suba――]

The girl who had broken into a jog to rush over to him from the other direction was about to call out, but Subaru, without slowing down, went ahead and embraced her, rendering her silent. 

With his arms now at their proper original size, he tightly hugged her slender body――,

Subaru: [――EMT.]

Emilia: […Idiot.]

Subaru had embraced her head-on, and Emilia, who was slightly surprised, smiled knowing that there was no helping it.

Their reunion in the Vollachian Empire had, of course, been exhilarating. Upon reuniting with her after being separated, Subaru had truly realized the depth of his feelings for her.

But, this time was, after all, different. ――This time, Natsuki Subaru was whole, mind, body and soul. 

Emilia: [Welcome back, Subaru.]

Subaru: [Yeah. ――I’m back, Emilia-tan.]

Emilia, who had sensed that same fulfillment of Subaru’s soul, spoke thus.

And then, beyond the two sharing in the joy of their reunion, the dazzling Crystal Palace, had burst into flames. 

 ――For the long, long-drawn Great Disaster of the Vollachian Empire, that was the closing ceremony.
